node.text:
@robbywclark has built a small empire with a scalable real estate business model🏡

When selecting markets to invest in, Robby believes it’s important to focus on the future needs of the city & where it’s headed as opposed to what its current state may be. He takes the same long-view approach to other industries & assets 📈

Over the next decade, he's betting on crypto, renewable energy, commodity metals and space🚀

Go to @Robbywclark's page to take your financial literacy to the next level!💰

node.title: Robby’s Rantz Episode 9 - Markets to Invest In with @tyga

node.text:
What exactly does it mean to work smart, not hard? 🧠 Allow me a moment of your time to explain...⁣
⁣
(First of all big credit to @successpictures for this image).⁣
⁣
We can all understand the concept that a sphere is easier to push than a square, but what can we do to work smarter in the real world?⁣
⁣
One good way to work smarter is to outsource things that are below your hourly pay.⁣
⁣
For example, if you can make $30/hour from a side hustle/job/business, and there's some task you have to do that would cost you $5/hour to outsource to a virtual assistant, do it! ⁣
⁣
This is working smarter, not harder. And with your extra time you can either make even more money or focus on other things.⁣
⁣
Another way to work smart, not hard is to set up systems you can then follow to produce results.⁣
⁣
For example, if you had to deliver 100 packages in one day, you could either haphazardly go from order to order without checking the location and work really hard to get it all done.⁣
⁣
Or you could set up a system whereby you sort the order destinations by their distance from each other. This way you can get your deliveries done in much less time. ⁣
⁣
Work smart (and hard) and you'll produce the most optimal results.⁣
⁣
Don't miss a post 👉 @investearnsave⁣

Jim Carey isn't a psychologist and this definitely isn't the only cause of depression, however...⁣
⁣
Being untrue to yourself will depress you and stress you out.⁣
⁣
Keeping up an appearance, trying to be something you're not.⁣
⁣
One of humanity's greatest assets is how different we all are to each other. These differences allow us to progress, develop new ideas and technologies and learn new things.⁣
⁣
Don't try to resist your difference.⁣
⁣
Don't seek to be average or normal.⁣
⁣
Be your authentic self.⁣
⁣
It's good for your mind and it's good for the world.⁣
⁣⁣⁣

node.text:
This is a very powerful message, let me add a caveat...⁣
⁣
There's a difference between cutting off a bad idea/project and quitting. ⁣
⁣
For example, if you made a dropshipping store and after testing it out you got not sales. It's not quitting to then try a different product with a new store and close the old one.⁣
⁣
Also goes with habits.⁣
⁣
If you try cycling to get fit, but you don't enjoy it. It's not quitting if you try swimming instead to get fit.⁣
⁣
Sometimes you gotta shake things up and cut off some projects/habits. But as long as you replace them with something positive, you aint quit.⁣
⁣⁣

node.text:
This doesn't mean you can't have anything nice!...⁣
⁣
It just means you get it for you, not to impress society.⁣
⁣
For example, I bought a fast car because I've always wanted a fast car. I enjoy driving, I enjoy driving more with this car.⁣
⁣
But I don't really enjoy fashion. So I would never buy expensive designer brands just to impress people. Stretching my budget to Nike is about as far as I go.⁣
⁣
So, it's okay to have some expensive things you buy.⁣
⁣
As long as you're buying them for you, not to impress people.⁣
⁣
This allows you to save and invest so much money so you can get the things that matter to you.⁣
⁣⁣
